raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "opentelemetry-instrumentation-httpx" %}
{% set version = "0.30b1" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/opentelemetry-instrumentation-httpx-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a74da63d32741ac7c4f9e52dba0bd647c61fdddfb504db842096857156ebe69a

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - opentelemetry-api ~=1.3
    - opentelemetry-instrumentation ==0.30b1
    - opentelemetry-semantic-conventions ==0.30b1
    - python >=3.6
    - wrapt <2.0.0,>=1.0.0
    # - respx ~=0.17.0
    # - opentelemetry-test ==0.24b0
    # - opentelemetry-sdk ~=1.3
    # - httpx <0.19.0,>=0.18.0
    # - respx ~=0.17.0
    # - opentelemetry-test ==0.25b0
    # - opentelemetry-sdk ~=1.3
    # - httpx <0.19.0,>=0.18.0
    # - respx ~=0.17.0

    # - respx ~=0.17.0
    # - opentelemetry-test ==0.25b2
    # - opentelemetry-sdk ~=1.3
    # - httpx <0.19.0,>=0.18.0
    # - respx ~=0.17.0
    # - opentelemetry-test-utils ==0.26b1
    # - opentelemetry-sdk ~=1.3
    # - httpx <0.19.0,>=0.18.0
    # - respx ~=0.17.0
    # - opentelemetry-test-utils ==0.27b0

test:

    - opentelemetry
    - opentelemetry.instrumentation
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:

extra:
